Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.parse.ParseQuery.getUserQuery()
    Please use ParseUser.getQuery() instead.
    com.parse.ParseObject.refresh()
    Please use ParseObject.fetch() instead.
    com.parse.ParseObject.refreshInBackground(RefreshCallback)
    Please use ParseObject.fetchInBackground(GetCallback) instead.
    com.parse.ParsePush.setPushToAndroid(boolean)
    Please use ParsePush.setQuery(ParseQuery) with a ParseQuery targeting ParseInstallations with a constraint on the deviceType field. If you use #setPushToAndroid(boolean) or ParsePush.setPushToIOS(boolean), then you will only be able to send to one of these two device types (e.g. and not Windows).
    com.parse.ParsePush.setPushToIOS(boolean)
    Please use ParsePush.setQuery(ParseQuery) with a ParseQuery targeting ParseInstallations with a constraint on the deviceType field. If you use #setPushToIOS(boolean) or ParsePush.setPushToAndroid(boolean), then you will only be able to send to one of these two device types (e.g. and not Windows).
    com.parse.ParseAnalytics.trackAppOpened(Intent)
    Please use ParseAnalytics.trackAppOpenedInBackground(android.content.Intent) instead.
    com.parse.ParseAnalytics.trackEvent(String)
    Please use ParseAnalytics.trackEventInBackground(String) instead.
    com.parse.ParseAnalytics.trackEvent(String, Map<String, String>)
    Please use ParseAnalytics.trackEventInBackground(String, java.util.Map) instead.
